Create " Age Group" and "% BAC " Grouping Column 9

Step 1: Create grouping “Age Group” Columns 


1.     Select DUI_Faltalities table

2.     Right-click on the Age column from the field  

3.     Select New Group option from the menu.

4.     In the Groups dialog box Name the column “Age Group"

5.     Select the age you want group from "ungrouped value" box.

6.     Click Group and the item you selected will moved to the "Group and Member" box.

7.     Rename the group

               0 -15 Years

                    16 - 25 Years

                           26 - 35 Years

                           36 - 45 Years

                           46 - 55 Years

                           56 - 65 Years

                           66 - 75 Years

                           76 - 85 Years 

                           85 - 95 Years 

*Note: Since there is not much data have from age 95 -118 Years, I included these ages groups into 85-95 Years Categories.  


 Follow the gif below to Create Age Group Column









Step 2: Create grouping "% BAC" Column 


1.     Select DUI_Faltalities Column

2.     Right-click on the Blood Alcohol column from the field  

3.     Select New Group option from the menu.

4.     In the Groups dialog box Name the column “% BAC"

5.     Select the Values of % BAC from ungrouped value.  

6.     Click group and the item you selected will moved to the Group and Member box.

7.     Rename the group.

                          0.000 - 0.100 % BAC

                                       0.101 - 0.200 % BAC

                                       0.201 - 0.300 % BAC

                                       0.301 - 0.400 % BAC

                                       0.401 - 0.500 % BAC

                                       0.501 - 0.600 % BAC

                                       0.601 - 0.700 % BAC


Follow the gif below to Create % BAC Column
